# Valid Anagram â€” Dictionary / Hashmap Approach

## Problem
Check if two strings `s` and `t` are anagrams without using sorting.

## Approach
- Use a dictionary (hashmap) to count characters in `s`
- Decrease counts while scanning `t`
- If any count goes below zero, return False
- Time complexity: O(n)
- Space complexity: O(1) (bounded by 26 letters or finite charset)

## Example
s = "anagram"
t = "nagaram"
Output: True
